SIMPLE: pitching
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Pitching
<hw>Pitch"ing</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The act of throwing
or casting; a cast; a pitch; <as>as, wild <ex>pitching</ex> in
baseball</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The rough paving of a street to a grade with blocks
of stone.</def> <rj><au>Mayhew.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Hydraul. Eng.)</fld> <def>A facing of stone laid
upon a bank to prevent wear by tides or currents.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Pitching piece</b></col> <fld>(Carp.)</fld>, <cd>the
horizontal timber supporting the floor of a platform of a stairway, and
against which the stringpieces of the sloping parts are
supported.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pitch-ore</ent>⟦br⟧
